```



  Do you have a config to change the cursor of the terminal 
Yes, you can configure the terminal cursor style in Zed's settings.json file. You can add the `terminal.cursor_style` property to customize the cursor appearance. Here are the available options:

```json
{
  "terminal": {
    "font_family": "MesloLGL Nerd Font",
    "cursor_style": "block" // You can use: "block", "bar", or "underline"
  }
}
```

So you can modify your existing settings.json file to include the cursor style like this:

```json
{
  "assistant": {
    "default_model": {
      "provider": "zed.dev",
      "model": "claude-3-5-sonnet-latest"
    },
    "version": "2"
  },
  "ui_font_size": 12,
  "buffer_font_size": 12,
  "ui_font_family": "MesloLGL Nerd Font",
  "theme": {
    "mode": "system",
    "light": "Atelier Sulphurpool Dark",
    "dark": "One Dark"
  },
  "terminal": {
    "font_family": "MesloLGL Nerd Font",
    "cursor_style": "block" // Choose between "block", "bar", or "underline"
  }
}
```

Choose the style that you prefer:
- `block`: A solid rectangular block cursor
- `bar`: A vertical line cursor
- `underline`: A horizontal line under the text
